3 Award WINS and 2 NOMINATIONS - including SXSW Audience Award Winner

Shot on video in and around Los Angeles's bohemian Silver Lake district, Charlotte Sometimes is a small, subtle character study about a young Asian-American, Michael, who repairs cars by day and by night manages a small apartment building that belongs to his aunt. One of his tenants is Lori, a sweet, girlish aspiring actress with whom Michael is secretly in love, but he is distracted by the aggressive, mysterious Darcy. Like the French filmmaker Eric Rohmer, director Eric Byler keeps his camera at a discreet distance from his actors, declining the easy emotional emphasis of close-ups in favor of the complex interaction of two actors sharing the same frame.


